(15, '20210427061308223.jpg', 'Verified Health Product Declaration ', '', '', 'verified-health-product-declaration-hpd', '<h3>Dinoflex Achieves First Third-Party Verified Health Product Declarations (HPDs) for Recycled Rubber Flooring </h3>\r\n\r\n<p><em><strong>By using one of the most sustainable materials available, Dinoflex has developed a unique manufacturing process to create the world\'s highest quality recycled rubber flooring system, and the first recycled rubber flooring products to have their HPDs third-party verified by SCS Global Services. </strong></em>  </p>\r\n\r\n<p><img alt=\"\" src=\"https://dinoflex.com/admin_upload/images/HPD.png\"></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>For Immediate Release</strong>   <br>\r\nFebruary 25, 2021, Salmon Arm, British Columbia – Dinoflex, a global industry leader in recycled rubber flooring, announced today that the company has successfully prepared and third-party verified Health Product Declarations (HPDs) for the collections Evolution, Sport Mat, Nature’s Collection, Vulca-No!, Walk Soft, Next Step, Stride, PlayTiles, and NuVista. Verified by SCS Global Services, an International leader in sustainability certifications, the HPDs are the only verified HPDs available for recycled rubber flooring.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>“A common misconception of recycled rubber flooring is that it does not allow the AEC community to achieve their goals of creating healthy living and working spaces for the people that occupy them. Along with our Floor Score® Certification for indoor air quality, our EPD certification and now successfully achieving our HPD certification, we are breaking down those barriers and providing viable, and more often than not, preferrable options for the design community.  At Dinoflex we know rubber is highly sustainable and an easily recyclable material,” said Mark Bunz, CEO, Dinoflex Group.  Adding, “Dinoflex is committed to producing recycled rubber flooring that is as sustainable in its production as it is effective in its application, and this new HPD certification validates our approach as we continue our innovative method to recycled rubber flooring.”  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dinoflex’s innovative approach to product development recognized that consumers around the world generate well over one billion waste tires every year, many of which end up in landfills or are burned, endlessly polluting our precious land, air and water resources. Dinoflex has taken countless tires out of landfills and repurposed them into beautiful, durable, FloorScore® certified solutions that qualify for valuable LEED® credits. Dinoflex offers a wide range of both interior flooring and exterior surfacing solutions for commercial, institutional, sport, and hospitality applications.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>Dinoflex is pleased to join the HPD Collaborative and their members sharing a common purpose to improve the transparency of information and the material health of the built environment. Using a consensus-based, stakeholder process, HPDC members create, support and evolve the HPD Open Standard.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Architects, designers, engineers, contractors, and specifiers can learn moreabout Dinoflex’s HPD certified recycled rubber flooring here: <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/home#loaded\">https://dinoflex.com/home#loaded</a>.   </p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>About Dinoflex </strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>For over 30 years Dinoflex has been a leading innovator in the manufacturing of recycled rubber surfacing products. The company specializes in producing premium quality recycled rubber flooring, surfaces, tiles and custom products. Their innovative products provide solutions for architects, designers and builders that are cost effective and environmentally friendly.  </p>\r\n\r\n<p>It is through constant research and development and the tireless pursuit of innovation that the company remains at the forefront of the industries it serves. Their unique process produces an impressive range of richly coloured flooring suitable for a multitude of sport and commercial applications and can be customized with intricate logos and designs. The company is proud to offer a product that is of the highest quality and helps make the world a more liveable space. To learn more about Dinoflex, their history, and products please visit <a href=\"https://www.dinoflex.com/\">https://www.dinoflex.com</a></p>\r\n', 'Dinoflex Recycled Rubber Flooring', '2021-02-24', 1, '2021-02-24 09:08:34', '2021-04-27 06:13:08'),
(16, '20210427062016715.jpg', 'Optimal commercial recycled rubber flooring options', 'Optimal Commercial Recycled Rubber Flooring Options', '', 'optimal-commercial-recycled-rubber-flooring-options', '<p><span xss=\"removed\">We live in a material world. A world where tall skyscrapers, flashy cars, and Parisian couture garner attention. So, it seems odd the one material that provides the foundation for all those things would be an afterthought.</span></p>\r\n<p><span><span xss=\"removed\">\r\n<img alt=\"Top 6 uses of rubber mat flooring\" src=\"https://dinoflex.com/admin_upload/images/img-sofa.jpg\" xss=\"removed\"></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nIt’s time to give a shout-out to the flooring that supports your first and last rep at the gym; the flooring that not only suppresses sound but also absorbs the shock as your weights drop to the ground.  We don’t often think about the flooring that provides underfoot comfort and support as you stand on your feet all day while at work, or the flooring that allows you to walk in comfort through a museum. Lastly, we don’t give much thought to the flooring that lets kids be kids and softens the falls that are inevitable on the playground. But flooring is a big deal, thus, making the right selection is paramount.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nThere are six key factors to take into consideration when selecting flooring for a commercial space. Besides looking at aesthetics and design, safety to the end user, <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-Ranges-Durability\">durability</a>, application, cost, and environmental impact all come into play when considering a product. With this in mind, we would like to introduce you to the realm of <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> — a flooring option that checks the box of each one of these key factors.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nAs a global industry leader, we at Dinoflex pride ourselves in offering durable <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> that is Made Flat, Stays Flat™,  guaranteed never to curl. Why is this important? Read on to learn more.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\"><strong>Benefits of Recycled Rubber Flooring in Commercial Applications</strong></a></h2>\r\nChoosing <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> for a commercial space is the right choice for a flooring solution. After listing the various benefits associated with <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> that are listed below, it is easy to understand and appreciate why so many establishments choose this type of flooring.\r\n\r\n<ol>\r\n  <li><strong>Safety </strong><p>Creating a safe environment for every person that enters your space, whether that is an employee, a patron, student, and/or teammate, should be a top priority for any organization. At Dinoflex, our <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> products provide just that. The high-traction, moisture resistant, non-curling nature of our products lowers the probability of accidents related to slipping and falling. Additionally, the shock-absorbing nature inherent in <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> reduces stress on the muscles and joints.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"2\">\r\n  <li><strong> <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-Ranges-Durability\">Durability</a>  </strong><p>Our long-lasting <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> is durable enough to withstand high-volume traffic, repeated drops of heavy-weight materials, skate blades, high-heel shoes and more. Our products are so durable that even after heavy exposure, they maintain a new look. With a long lifespan this also means that after choosing <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> you will not have to worry about floor replacements for a very long time.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"3\">\r\n  <li><strong> Cost </strong><p>Installing <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> fits any budget. At DInoflex, we don’t impose minimum orders for your chosen product, we understand the value of installing our <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> in any space of any size. Taking that into consideration makes your choice easy especially when you also factor in the longevity of our <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"4\">\r\n  <li><strong> Aesthetic </strong><p>Say hello to <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/color-innovator/home\">‘The Color Innovator’</a>, a design software featured on our website that allows buyers to essentially mix and match approximately 60 EPDM colored granule options. This makes it even easier to install <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> that matches the overall aesthetic of any establishment. When you combine this with a custom inlaid logo, you’ll quickly understand the adaptability, versatility and convenience that <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> offers, and that it has come a long way from its stark black origins.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"5\">\r\n  <li><strong> Environmental Impact </strong><p>By taking used commercial truck tires that would have made their way into landfills and recycling them into new rubber flooring, it becomes quite clear that this is a great way to repurpose materials. At Dinoflex, we lessen the load on the environment and manufacture products that are not only durable and versatile, but also safe for the end user. This makes Dinoflex <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> an easy choice for any project in need of a flooring solution. We are the first recycled rubber manufacturer to obtain a third-party verified Health Product Declaration (HPD), which means the use of our products creates healthy living and working spaces for the people that occupy them.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"6\">\r\n  <li><strong> Ease of Use</strong><p>Get ready to roll up your sleeves, because the installation guides that accompany our easy-to-install products have been designed with the end-user in mind. This means, we strive to make it easy and simple to install our <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> in your facility.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Advantages-of-Using-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring\"><strong>Advantages of Using Recycled Rubber Flooring</strong></a></h2></span></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nWe have delineated the six key factors that you should consider when purchasing new flooring, however, let’s delve a little further into the sustainability of <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a>. Let’s begin where our products begin-at the land fill.  We harvest thousands of tires every year and knowing your flooring product is made of used commercial truck tires is an interesting concept.</span></p>\r\n<p><span><span xss=\"removed\"><img alt=\"Top 6 uses of rubber mat flooring\" src=\"https://dinoflex.com/admin_upload/images/img-gym.jpg\" xss=\"removed\"></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nWe begin by harvesting rubber tires that have been tossed to the landfills and grind them into gravel-size pieces. In our case, we strictly deal with one supplier so that we can ensure that the product that we receive meets our stringent standard of cleanliness. What does this mean? It means that the tire grinds undergo a three-stage sifting process where all the debris is thoroughly removed. Once the product arrives at our facility, we then have it sent through another sifting and cleaning stage. From there, the new raw product is mixed with polyurethane, molded into a block form, placed under high pressure, air-cured, and then precision sliced with a water jet cutter.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\n<p><strong>FloorScore Certified</strong></p>\r\nThe EPDM colored granules that we use are purchased from Germany and are considered to emit the lowest VOCs in the marketplace, which has led to our products gaining a FloorScore certification.</span></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\n<p><strong>Recyclable</strong></p>\r\nYes, our products can be recycled yet again. The fact that the interlocking tiles don’t require subfloor adhesives not only eliminates the odors associated with traditional adhesive products, but it allows the tiles to be easily removed and replaced when the time comes years down the line.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<p>\r\n<p><strong>Tire Stewardship Grant Eligible</strong></p>\r\nThe Tire Stewardship grant has helped cover the cost of installation for many customers — this acts as an incentive to implement <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a>.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Why-You-Need-High-Quality-Flooring\"><strong>Why You Need High-Quality Flooring </strong></a></h2>\r\nCertain products gain more appeal with a faded, used, distressed look. While we can appreciate a worn-in-look in many applications, the idea of being able to map out the high-traffic areas of your commercial space isn’t acceptable. This gives your space the appearance of being tired, outdated, and unkempt. Though wear-and-tear is a fact of life, there are products that are more resilient than others.\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p> \r\nCue our <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a>. Manufactured to withstand decades of use, this long-lasting flooring type will not only look great for years to come but will provide a high- traction and safe foundation for the feet that traverse it. Best of all, our products are made flat to stay flat.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Why-Commercial-Areas-Must-Have-Easy-to-Clean-Floors\"><strong>Why Commercial Areas Must Have Easy-to-Clean Floors<a></strong></h2>\r\nWith a checklist in hand, the practice of enforcing the maintenance of a clean <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Why-Commercial-Areas-Must-Have-Easy-to-Clean-Floors\">commercial space</a> has been the enduring agenda of every health and safety inspector. An inadequate score can often lead to the demise of an otherwise burgeoning business. It’s of the utmost importance that when anyone steps foot into an establishment, they are able to do so on a <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Why-Commercial-Areas-Must-Have-Easy-to-Clean-Floors\">clean floor</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p> \r\nUnsanitary conditions can be customer-repelling for a business and cleanliness is a key component of safety. The onslaught of COVID-19 has certainly kicked that instinct into overdrive. With this in mind, it is now more important than ever that the curators of <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Why-Commercial-Areas-Must-Have-Easy-to-Clean-Floors\">commercial spaces </a> implement the installation of <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Why-Commercial-Areas-Must-Have-Easy-to-Clean-Floors\">easy-to-clean flooring</a> materials such as the recycled rubber products from\r\n<a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/\">Dinoflex</a></p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-Ranges-Durability\"><strong>Recycled Rubber Flooring Ranges and Durability </strong></a></h2>\r\nFrom fitness centers that aim to enhance the body, to ski hills and hockey arenas that motivate us to move, or to education facilities that stimulate the mind, there is one common denominator — Dinoflex <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a>. The versatility and <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-Ranges-Durability\">durability</a> of our products make them an ideal flooring solution for a variety of commercial applications.\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Fitness </strong><p>Customers like the fitness fanatics at CrossFit Vernon and No Limits Fitness drop some serious weight on their floors. The Salmon Arm Silverbacks hockey team have proven that skate blades may cut-up the ice but are no match for the durable nature of Dinoflex <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a>. Flooring like our Sport Mat or Next Step High Impact have been installed in gyms and arenas, allowing these floors to still look new after years of less-than-delicate interactions.</p></li>\r\n\r\n  <li><strong>Education </strong><p>The Royal Tyrrell Museum of Palaentology (RTM) features one of the world’s largest dinosaur installations and plays host to nearly half a million visitors each year. However, you would never know it by looking at its floors. The normal traffic patterns that can be seen on the floors in many similar facilities are virtually non-existent. With that empirical data and the visitor comfort our flooring provides, RTM has continued to incorporate Dinoflex <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> during each expansion of the museum </p></li>\r\n\r\n  <li><strong>Hospitality </strong><p>Boasting over 3.6 million crystals, Sparkling Hill Resort was the first hotel in North America to incorporate crystal-infused architecture. When it came time to select flooring that would complement such a unique aesthetic, Dinoflex <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> was the winner, proving that rubber flooring is not only durable but attractive as well. We installed our <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> tiles throughout their facility and being fully customizable with color, we allow you to unleash your creative side to perfectly match your facility.</p></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Most Used Indoor Commercial Flooring Applications </strong></h2>\r\nRegardless of space and function, our <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> can be applied in a variety of spaces. The most common flooring applications of Dinoflex products are\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Gyms and Fitness centres</strong> </li>\r\n  <li><strong>Pharmacies</strong></li>\r\n  <li><strong>Museums</strong></li>\r\n  <li><strong>Ski resorts</strong></li>\r\n  <li><strong>Offices and Retail spaces</strong></li>\r\n  <li><strong>Hospitality</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<H2><a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Customize-Flooring-Space-with-Dinoflex-Solutions\"><strong>Customize to Any Space</strong></a></h2>\r\nWith a range of color and use options, Dinoflex <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a> has become a favourite among architects, builders, and interior designers. Whether a space is large — airports, aquatic centres, military bases, museums, or arenas — or small — art galleries, call centers, daycares, libraries, or pet facilities, be it indoors or outdoors, the versatile nature of our flooring leaves no project behind. We can see this assertion in action when we look at the following two examples:\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>When the folks at Bay Resource Group decided to revamp the 6,000 square foot rooftop of one of their condominiums, they used Dinoflex recycled tight-lock rubber tiles to create an aerial oasis for the complex\'s inhabitants.</li>\r\n  <li>The cool kids at Mastermind Studios were looking to install soundproof flooring and walls to house production stages. It was clear that our product was the affordable, easy, and effective solution that they had been searching for.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Our extensive list of products suit any spec of project that is at hand, and we make it even easier because Dinoflex does not implement a minimum-order on our products. </p>\r\n\r\n<h2><a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Indoor-Commercial-Flooring-QA\"><strong>Indoor Commercial Flooring Q&A </strong></a></h2>\r\n<p><strong>What is vulcanization?</strong></p><p>Vulcanization is the process by which rubber gains its <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-Ranges-Durability\">durability</a>. Traditionally, this process used sulfur to aid in the hardening of natural rubber. However, as time has progressed, the term now refers to other treatments that provide added strength to synthetic rubbers.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is a VOC?</strong> </p>\r\n<p>Volatile Organic Compounds (VOCs) are toxic gases that some materials release into the air, which can lead to respiratory difficulty as well as many other health complications. </p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is FloorScore certified?</strong></p>\r\n<p>FloorScore has been touted as “the most recognized <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Indoor-Commercial-Flooring-QA\">indoor</a> air quality (IAQ) certification standard for hard surface flooring materials, adhesives, and underlayment. This voluntary certification tests flooring products to ascertain whether they contain one or more of thirty-five VOC emissions.’</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>What is HPD?</strong></p><p>At Dinoflex, we are committed to producing <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\"><a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications\">recycled rubber flooring</a></a> that is as sustainable in its production as it is effective in its application. We are proud to be the first recycled rubber manufacturer to attain a third-party verified Health Product Declaration (HPD). This means, with our collective designations, we are creating healthy living and working spaces. </p>\r\n<p> \r\n\r\nDinoflex’s <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/Why-You-Need-High-Quality-Flooring\">high-quality flooring</a> may be the only thing that you love that gives you permission to walk all over it! With this in mind, it’s time to lay a recycled rubber floored way to another exhibit, fitness machine, and classroom. At Dinoflex, we’re ready to assist you with just about any flooring project that you may have. You can contact us by visiting our website   <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/contact\">here.</a> Alternatively, you can call us directly at (250) 832-7780 or toll-free at (877) 713-1899.</span></p>', 'Dinoflex Recycled Rubber Flooring', '2021-04-08', 1, '2021-04-08 07:16:26', '2021-06-23 01:39:38'),
(17, '20210522010007414.jpg', 'Benefits of Recycled Rubber Flooring in Commercial Applications', '', 'Benefits of Recycled Rubber Flooring in Commercial Applications', 'Benefits-of-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring-in-Commercial-Applications', '<p><span xss=\"removed\">Recycled rubber flooring is rapidly gaining popularity in a range of settings, including  commercial applications. The benefits of installing recycled rubber flooring in your establishment are vast, and if you are trying to decide between different types of flooring options for your commercial space, Dinoflex has a solution for you. We stand firm in our commitment that our recycled rubber flooring systems can provide you with everything you are looking for and more. \r\n</span></p> \r\n<p><span><span xss=\"removed\">\r\n<img alt=\"Top 6 uses of rubber mat flooring\" src=\"https://dinoflex.com/admin_upload/images/b1.jpg\" xss=\"removed\"></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<h2>6 Benefits of Rubber Flooring Options for Your Commercial Space</h2></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nEven though you may not give it much thought, choosing the right type of flooring is paramount – it can offer comfort, support and even help soften falls. Recycled rubber flooring in particular offers six potential benefits that can be appealing for a wide variety of commercial applications: \r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>Safety: </strong> Our recycled rubber flooring products offer superior slip-resistance which is especially suitable for many high-traffic, commercial environments. In addition to being a high-traction material, our recycled rubber flooring also repels moisture and is non-curling. These qualities help prevent accidents and injuries.</li>  \r\n<li><strong> Durability:</strong>  One of the most obvious advantages of recycled rubber flooring is its durability. Rubber is inherently resilient and can withstand a variety of conditions including high-traffic and heavy exposure settings. It can also reduce noise and vibrations. A properly-cared for recycled rubber flooring system can last for several years and continue to maintain its visual appeal. </li>\r\n<li><strong> Cost:</strong>  Contrary to popular belief, recycled rubber flooring is suitable for every budget, which is especially true when you shop for recycled rubber flooring systems at Dinoflex. If you are happy with your chosen product, you don’t have to worry about any minimum size for your order. We recognize the value of installing recycled rubber flooring no matter the size of your commercial space. </li>\r\n<li> <strong>Aesthetic: </strong> If you are looking for customization, we can help. Using our innovative design software, you can make sure that the flooring you choose will complement the rest of your aesthetic. We can even incorporate a custom inlaid logo into the floor of your choosing. </li>\r\n<li> <strong>Environmental Impact: </strong> Rubber is recyclable as well as extremely eco-friendly. Not only are our products versatile and durable, they also lessen the impact on the environment because they do not include any harmful additives.</li> \r\n<li> <strong>Ease of Use:</strong> Our products are designed with the end-user in mind and are always delivered with an easy-to-follow installation guide. Additionally, once your recycled rubber flooring is installed, it is very easy to maintain. </li>\r\n</ol>\r\nAfter 30 years as a global industry leader, here at Dinoflex we continue to offer commercial clients, including architects, designers and builders, a diverse collection of interior and exterior floor covering solutions that are truly something to be proud of. Our goal is to provide you with an exclusive line of innovative <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/products\">products</a> to help you create both practical, unique and creative spaces.\r\n</span></p> \r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\n <strong>\r\nFor more information about our recycled rubber flooring products for commercial applications, or to order yours today, contact us by calling our toll-free number at 877-713-1899 or fill out our online <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/contact\">contact form </a>and we will be happy to assist you as soon as possible.</strong></span></p>\r\n', 'Dinoflex Recycled Rubber Flooring', '2021-05-22', 1, '2021-05-22 01:00:07', '2021-05-22 04:27:10'),
(18, '20210522011548537.jpg', 'Advantages of Using Recycled Rubber Flooring ', 'Advantages of Using Recycled Rubber Flooring ', '', 'Advantages-of-Using-Recycled-Rubber-Flooring', '<p><span xss=\"removed\">Recycled rubber flooring is a preferred flooring option for both residential and commercial applications, and with good reason. Since rubber is an extremely durable, easy to maintain and long-lasting material, it is already quite a popular flooring choice in places like gyms and childcare settings. Being an economic investment, recycled rubber as a flooring solution offers many advantages (this will link for Cluster Blog 1 for April), making it a sound-long term investment. It is also a great alternative to even more expensive and hard to maintain flooring options like wood or tile. Read on to find out more about the advantages of recycled rubber flooring. </span></p>\r\n<p><span><span xss=\"removed\">\r\n<img alt=\"Top 6 uses of rubber mat flooring\" src=\"https://dinoflex.com/admin_upload/images/b2.jpg\" xss=\"removed\"></span></span></p>\r\n<p> \r\n<h2>Why is it Important to Choose High-Quality Recycled Rubber Flooring? </h2></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nRecycled rubber flooring is the perfect surface, suitable for a variety of uses and applications. At DInoflex, we manufacture the highest quality recycled rubber flooring, ideal for any space of any size. With recycled rubber flooring from Dinoflex, you can expect: \r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>  Guaranteed Durability: </strong> Rubber is a strong material that can withstand heavy use and high-traffic zones. When you invest in high-quality recycled rubber flooring, you know you are getting a long-lasting product that will be worth the investment.</li>  \r\n<li><strong>  Easy to Care For:</strong> Quality recycled rubber flooring is stain-resistant and easy to maintain. Most high-quality recycled rubber flooring simply requires cleaning using no more than a damp cloth to wipe away dirt, dust and other debris.  </li>\r\n<li><strong>  Customize Your Flooring: </strong> The look of your recycled rubber flooring will vary depending on the quality. When you invest in high-quality recycled rubber flooring with Dinoflex, you can choose from a wide range of options and even customize your flooring to your preferred colours and logo.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<h2>Tips on How to Pick the Right Recycled Rubber Floor</h2>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nShopping for the right recycled rubber floor has the potential to get confusing without proper guidance. Fortunately at Dinoflex, we make it easy to select the ideal solution for any project in any space. Here are a few essential tips to remember when picking out your recycled rubber floor: \r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>  Consider Your Budget: </strong> When evaluating your recycled rubber flooring options, the desire to go with the nicest looking design can be very tempting. At Dinoflex, you don’t have to sacrifice esthetics and design for price-we make it affordable to have a stunning and durable floor in any space.</li>\r\n<li> <strong> Understand the Purpose: </strong> Before picking out your recycled rubber floor, understand the space and purpose in which it will be laid. We have a variety of flooring options, each one ideal and suitable for the venue in which it is placed.</li>\r\n<li> <strong> Choosing a Thickness:</strong>  One of the most important decisions you will have to make regarding your recycled rubber flooring is choosing its thickness. Generally, the thicker the rubber, the more durable your floor will be. </li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nAt Dinoflex, we specialize in manufacturing durable, eco-friendly and cost-effective recycled rubber flooring <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/products\"> products</a>, formatted as rubber mats and rubber tiles. As a global industry leader, we offer you direct access to the highest quality commercial recycled rubber flooring so you can be confident in the longevity and sustainability of our product in the space for which it is chosen.</span></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\"> \r\n <strong>\r\nFor more information about our recycled rubber flooring products or to order yours today, contact us by calling our toll-free number at 877-713-1899 or fill out our online <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/contact\">contact form</a> and we will be happy to assist you as soon as possible.</strong></span></p>\r\n\r\n\r\n', 'Dinoflex Recycled Rubber Flooring', '2021-05-22', 1, '2021-05-22 01:15:48', '2021-05-22 04:29:41'),
(19, '20210522012853899.jpg', 'Why You Need High-Quality Flooring', 'Why You Need High-Quality Flooring', '', 'Why-You-Need-High-Quality-Flooring', '<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nHigh-quality flooring is important for both home and business owners alike. Unlike rugs that can be easily swapped out when necessary, flooring is a more permanent fixture in your space and is the most used surface in any building. As a result, the right type of flooring is critical and no matter what type of flooring option you choose, it should be of dependable quality. If you want to make sure that your floors are durable enough to withstand constant foot traffic, resist moisture, are easy to maintain and complement your existing aesthetic, consider installing high-quality recycled rubber flooring from Dinoflex.</span></p> <p><span><span xss=\"removed\">\r\n<img alt=\"Top 6 uses of rubber mat flooring\" src=\"https://dinoflex.com/admin_upload/images/b3.jpg\" xss=\"removed\"></span></span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<h2>High-Quality Recycled Rubber Flooring Offers Great Value</h2></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nThere are several factors to consider when shopping for recycled rubber flooring products. Taking your time to make the right choice can ensure that you are left with a surface that meets all your expectations when it comes to quality and design. Here are a few ways high-quality recycled rubber flooring offers great value: \r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong>  Increases Safety: </strong> The safety of your employees and customers is crucial. A high-quality recycled rubber floor ensures that the chances of slips and falls are greatly reduced. Even if the occasional accident occurs, the softer surface provides enough cushion to help individuals avoid major injuries. </li>\r\n<li> <strong> Encourages Productivity: </strong> Recycled rubber flooring limits noise distraction, helping those in the area focus on their work. Since high-quality flooring can help absorb noise, this can also make transactions between employees and customers much more comfortable and convenient.  </li>\r\n<li> <strong> Reflects Positively on Your Business: </strong> Investing in high-quality recycled rubber flooring is one way to demonstrate to employees, clients and customers that you expect and maintain a high level of professionalism. Low-quality flooring may imply the opposite and demonstrate your lack of commitment to your business image. </li> \r\n</ol>\r\n</span>\r\n</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<h2>Most Economical Options for Busy Locations</h2></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nThe durability and subsequent longevity of our products here at Dinoflex makes recycled rubber flooring the most economical option for busy locations.\r\n<ol>\r\n<li> When compared to natural or synthetic rubbers, recycled rubber is much more affordable.</li> \r\n<li> Low manufacturing costs and less energy consumption keep the costs of recycled rubber flooring down.</li>\r\n<li> Recycled rubber flooring is stronger and more durable, providing you with years of optimum performance in high traffic areas. </li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\">\r\nAt Dinoflex, we specialize in providing our customers with durable, sustainable and affordable recycled rubber flooring. Our goal is to make your facility safe, more environmentally friendly and compliant by offering high-quality recycled rubber surfacing <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/products\">products</a>. We are passionate about giving customers an alternative flooring solution that enhances interior décor and also offers the durability that is necessary to support your day-to-day activities. </span></p>\r\n<p><span xss=\"removed\"><strong>\r\nFor more information about our recycled rubber flooring products for commercial applications, or to order yours today, contact us by calling our toll-free number at 877-713-1899. You can also fill out our online <a href=\"https://dinoflex.com/contact\">contact form</a> and we will be happy to assist you as soon as possible.</strong></span></p>\r\n', 'Dinoflex Recycled Rubber Flooring', '2021-05-22', 1, '2021-05-22 01:28:53', '2021-05-22 04:28:03'),
